# Mollen Infrastructure

This repository contains the Docker Compose configuration for all Mollen services.

## Services
- Farm to School Website (Frontend + Backend)
- NodeBB Forum
- MongoDB
- Vaultwarden
- PostgreSQL

## Setup
1. Clone this repository
2. Copy `.env.example` to `.env` and fill in secure passwords
3. Clone service repositories in the same parent directory:
   ```bash
   cd ..
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/FarmToSchoolWebsite
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/FarmToSchoolForum
   ```
4. Start all services:
   ```bash
   docker-compose up -d
   ```

## Development
- Each service's source code lives in its own repository
- This repo only contains infrastructure configuration
- Use docker-compose.override.yml for local development settings

## First Run
1. Set up NodeBB admin account:
   ```bash
   docker-compose exec forum ./nodebb setup
   ```
2. Initialize Vaultwarden database:
   ```bash
   docker-compose exec vaultwarden ./vaultwarden
   ```
